P6 - RAID Degraded Incident Summary

1. Create project directory

mkdir P6-RAID-Degraded-Lab
cd P6-RAID-Degraded-Lab

2. Verify RAID management tool is available

which mdadm

3. Create two disk image files

dd if=/dev/zero of=disk1.img bs=1M count=200
dd if=/dev/zero of=disk2.img bs=1M count=200

4. Attach disk images to loop devices

sudo losetup -fP disk1.img
sudo losetup -fP disk2.img

5. Create a RAID1 array

sudo mdadm --create --verbose /dev/md0 --level=1 --raid-devices=2 /dev/loop0 /dev/loop1

6. Verify RAID status

cat /proc/mdstat

Example output:
[UU]

7. Simulate disk failure

sudo mdadm /dev/md0 --fail /dev/loop1

8. Remove failed disk

sudo mdadm /dev/md0 --remove /dev/loop1

9. Verify degraded RAID state

cat /proc/mdstat

Example output:
[_U]

10. Add replacement disk

sudo mdadm /dev/md0 --add /dev/loop1

11. Verify RAID recovery

cat /proc/mdstat

Expected result:
[UU]
